    public class SetupWindow
extends javafx.scene.layout.BorderPane
    This class shows the overlay for the game setup.
    The user can specify a party name and may overwrite the player name.
    A new party can be started, an existing party can be joined or a random party can be joined. In case of random joining will a new party be created, if no wating game is present on the server. If a party is startet, it can be defined whether this party is publicly available or private.

      • connect

        private void connect(boolean createGame,
                     boolean randomConnect,
                     boolean privateGame,
                     java.lang.String partyName,
                     java.lang.String playerName)
        Method establishes a connection to the server
        Parameters:
        createGame - If true, a new game will be created, otherwiese the client tries to connect to a waiting game
        randomConnect - If true, the client will try to connect to a random game (or create a new one, if no available).
        Otherwise it will create a game with the specified party name or will try to connect to a game with the specified party name
        privateGame - If true, a private game will be created in case of creating. This parameter is not applying if createGame is false.
        partyName - The name of the party
        playerName - The name of the Player
